cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CY

This paper deals with the annotation of a corpus of sentences for linguistic variables such as formality, informativeness, and implicature. This falls under the domain of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and natural language processing (NLP). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning algorithms for automatic stylistic scoring, which falls under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The study also involves analyzing the sentential make-up of a document in terms of style, which could be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and cybersecurity (cs.CY).
